    <p>‚ûû <strong>Total fan points distributed per user: 57 pts</strong></p>
    <p>These points are stored securely and used to create a <strong>global ranking</strong> of candidates based solely on how the public perceives their performance and preparation.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üåê Independence & Transparency</h2>
    <p>MyHotPicks is <strong>not affiliated</strong> with any official pageant organization, judge panel, or sponsor. We are a <strong>completely independent, fan-created platform</strong>. Our only objective is to give fans a tool to be heard.</p>
    <p>This is not a prediction game. It is not betting. It is not a contest. It is <strong>pure, open, transparent admiration</strong> expressed by the global audience.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>‚ù§Ô∏è A Call to Unity, Participation, and Celebration</h2>
    <p>We believe fans are a vital part of every pageant. We follow every candidate, we watch the rehearsals, we support the brands and sponsors, we observe every stage of the competition ‚Äî and we feel connected.</p>
    <blockquote><em>We are the ones who watch. We are the ones who care. We are the ones who cheer.</em></blockquote>
    <p>This platform exists to bring us together as <strong>one global fan voice</strong> ‚Äî a voice that recognizes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The hard work of every candidate</li>
      <li>The effort and organization behind each show</li>
      <li>The companies and sponsors who support them</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üëë Respect for the Official Crown</h2>
    <p>We fully respect the decisions of the official organizations. We celebrate every crowned queen, and we understand that there are many elements behind each final result ‚Äî technical, organizational, cultural, economic. That is part of the process.</p>
    <p>But as fans, we also want to admire and highlight what we see. We want to celebrate the journey, the presence, the preparation ‚Äî and express our admiration publicly. <strong>Not to oppose, but to complement the official decisions.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üß≠ Why this matters</h2>
